---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Overview" description="RankMySEO docs — install tree, support matrix, adapters, storage, and client demo.">
  <p class="pill">M5 ecosystem · shipped</p>
  <h1>RankMySEO reference</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    Composable SEO toolkit for Node.js apps. Bring your own database, framework, and (optionally) AI keys.
    This Astro site dogfoods <code>@rankmyseo/client</code> and documents the final M5 support matrix.
  </p>

  <div class="grid">
    <a class="card" href="/install">
      <h3>Install decision tree</h3>
      <p>Pick backend, storage, and UI packages for your stack.</p>
    </a>
    <a class="card" href="/matrix">
      <h3>Runtime support matrix</h3>
      <p>Node yes · edge/Workers no · React UI · Vue/Svelte headless.</p>
    </a>
    <a class="card" href="/adapters">
      <h3>Server adapters</h3>
      <p>Hono, Express, Next, Nitro, SvelteKit, Astro.</p>
    </a>
    <a class="card" href="/storage">
      <h3>Storage options</h3>
      <p>SQLite, Postgres (Drizzle), Prisma, Kysely.</p>
    </a>
    <a class="card" href="/regression">
      <h3>SEO regression CLI</h3>
      <p>Gate preview vs production with <code>regression check</code>.</p>
    </a>
    <a class="card" href="/demo">
      <h3>Client demo</h3>
      <p><code>createRankMySeoClient</code> with a mocked baseUrl.</p>
    </a>
  </div>

  <h2>Canonical wiki</h2>
  <p>
    Full docs live in the repo wiki source under <code>docs/wiki/</code>. Start with
    <a href="https://github.com/madebyaris/rankmyseo/wiki/Getting-Started">Getting Started</a>,
    <a href="https://github.com/madebyaris/rankmyseo/wiki/Packages">Packages</a>, and
    <a href="https://github.com/madebyaris/rankmyseo/wiki/SEO-Regression">SEO Regression</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Quick install</h2>
  <pre><code>npm i rankmyseo
npx rankmyseo install --yes --preset recommended
npx rankmyseo init
npx rankmyseo migrate
npx rankmyseo doctor --json</code></pre>
</BaseLayout>
